Package: HSMap
Type: Package
Title: Maternal Linkage Mapping in Open-Pollinated Diploid Families
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Marcelo", "Mollinari", email = "mmollina@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Kim", "McKeever", role = "aut"),
    person("Molly", "Irvin", role = "aut"),
    person("Fikret", "Isik", role = "aut")
  )
Description: A fast C++ (Rcpp) maternal hidden Markov model for building linkage
             maps in open-pollinated (unknown-sire) diploid half-sib families. The
             unknown paternal contribution is integrated out through a per-marker,
             dam-specific paternal gametic frequency; several dams are combined by a
             joint EM that estimates one shared recombination map while keeping phase
             and the paternal model dam-specific. Maps are fitted within resolved phase
             blocks, and no-linkage intervals are reported as gaps rather than large
             centimorgan distances.
